# ║  CHANGE REGISTRY v3.30.26.1                                             ║
# ║                                                                          ║
# ║  FEAT-LI-001  Label Inspector tab                                        ║
# ║    New "🏷 Label Inspector" notebook tab + LabelInspectorWindow          ║
# ║    Toplevel class. Lets operator browse any YOLO dataset root,           ║
# ║    navigate images in train/val splits, see the YOLO box overlaid on    ║
# ║    the image, view and edit the paired .txt label file inline, and       ║
# ║    save with automatic timestamped backup.  Class ID audit               ║
# ║    (audit_and_fix_label_class_ids) runs before any label save.          ║
# ║                                                                          ║
# ║  FEAT-DBG-001  Enhanced detection overlay: 3 independently toggleable   ║
# ║    layers in QCViewer                                                    ║
# ║    Previously a single "📦 Show Boxes [B]" toggle drew only the         ║
# ║    detection/SpotBox rectangle.  Now three independent checkboxes:       ║
# ║      • [B] YOLO Box  — raw YOLO xyxy output (large, context box)       ║
# ║      • [P] SpotBox   — SpotBoxSize×SpotBoxSize extraction region        ║
# ║      • [H] Hotspot   — exact hotspot pixel from extraction metadata      ║
# ║    Colours: YOLO=cyan, SpotBox=yellow, Hotspot=red.                      ║
# ║    JSON extraction block parsed for spot_box and hotspot_pixel fields.  ║
# ║    All three layers are independent; existing keyboard shortcut B        ║
# ║    continues to toggle YOLO box layer.                                   ║
# ║                                                                          ║
# ║  FEAT-QCJSON-001  QC-edited JSONs routed to qc_jsons/ subfolder         ║
# ║    _write_json() previously wrote to detection_jsons/ (same folder as   ║
# ║    the pipeline output), making it impossible to distinguish QC edits   ║
# ║    from auto-detection output.  Fix: QC-edited JSONs now written to     ║
# ║    detected_folder/qc_jsons/.  _json_path_for() checks qc_jsons/ first ║
# ║    so QC overrides always win over detection pipeline output.           ║
# ║                                                                          ║
# ║  FEAT-QCDIR-001  QCOutputFolder auto-creation                           ║
# ║    open_qc_viewer() previously silently fell back to the default        ║
# ║    visual_annotated/annotated/ path when QCOutputFolder was configured  ║
# ║    but the directory did not yet exist.  Fix: create the directory       ║
# ║    automatically so the first QC save lands in the configured location.  ║
# ║                                                                          ║
# ║  FEAT-MANIFEST-001  Folder manifests for all output subdirectories      ║
# ║    write_folder_manifest() writes a human-readable folder_manifest.json ║
# ║    the first time each output subfolder is created, explaining its       ║
# ║    purpose and JSON schema.  Covers: detection_jsons/, qc_jsons/,       ║
# ║    not_marked/jsons/, visual_annotated/visual/,                          ║
# ║    visual_annotated/annotated/, original_ir/, qc_output/.               ║
